#: /tmp/tmparbqp2c8.md:70
msgid ""
"The profile selection dialog disappears and then, Rolisteam is waiting for "
"other players to join. In the notification panel, **Rolisteam** gives you "
"all informations required to join your game. Players must have those "
"information ( ip address to join and port).  \n"
"Don't forget to give them the password as well."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmparbqp2c8.md:72
msgid "Step 3 : Connectivity test"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmparbqp2c8.md:73
msgid ""
"We strongly recommand to test the connection before your first game.\n"
"So we developed a [connection "
"test](http://www.rolisteam.org/php/test_ip.php) to know if your network let "
"incomming connections reach **Rolisteam**."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmparbqp2c8.md:75
msgid "Set the ip address and port on the webpage and click on `Test`."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmparbqp2c8.md:77
msgid ""
"The response should be **Good News ! Connection succeed!**.  \n"
"Any other response means it does not work."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmparbqp2c8.md:79
msgid "Connection failed ? don't worry"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmparbqp2c8.md:80
msgid ""
"The most frequent cause about connection issue is the separation between "
"your local network and the internet.  \n"
"In this case, the device on the internet is not your computer but it's your "
"network device (modem/router/...).  \n"
"So the incoming connection reaches your network device but it does not know "
"what to do with it.  "
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmparbqp2c8.md:82
msgid ""
"Settings rule to forward incoming connection to your computer fixes it. But "
"at First, we must be sure your computer has always the same address inside "
"your local network."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmparbqp2c8.md:84
msgid ""
"The configuration must be made once. When it had worked it should work "
"until you change your network device or erase its memory."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmparbqp2c8.md:86
msgid ""
"There are plenty of tutorials online, just search for **port forwarding** "
"and the name of your **ISP**."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmparbqp2c8.md:88
msgid "Fixed Ip address"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmparbqp2c8.md:89
msgid ""
"The process here is highly network device dependent or ISP dependent.  \n"
"On the network device configuration page, you must look for **dhcp**, "
"**local network rule** or **Lan**.\n"
"Set your computer to have always the same local Ip address (commonly "
"192.168.0.XXX or 192.168.1.XXX)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmparbqp2c8.md:91
msgid ""
"To make sure it works, unplug and replug your computer several times or "
"restart it and check that the local ip address does not change."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmparbqp2c8.md:93
msgid "Forwarding Connection"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmparbqp2c8.md:94
msgid ""
"This configuration steps are highly dependent of your network device.  \n"
"The goal here is to define a rule. This rule says: \"when an incoming "
"connection using the port 6660 reaches you (network device). Please forward "
"it to my computer's ip local address (previous step)\"."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmparbqp2c8.md:96
msgid ""
"Test your connection with the tool described ealier in this document. \n"
"When the connection works, you should give information to the other players."
msgstr ""

